{"title":"Easton 1x Direct Mount 12sp Chainrings Mate Cinch Cranks to GRX, 105, Ultegra & Dura-Ace","link":"https://bikerumor.com/easton-direct-mount-shimano-12-speed-1x-chainrings/","date":1694014603000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_40T-ring.jpg\" alt=\"Easton Direct Mount 1x GRX gravel chainrings for Shimano 12-speed HyperGlide+\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_40T-ring.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_40T-ring-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_40T-ring-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_40T-ring-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_40T-ring-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_40T-ring-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_40T-ring-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Now that Shimano <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-grx-12-speed-mechanical/\" target=\"_blank\">GRX</a> upgrades to 12-speed, Easton machines new aftermarket direct mount 1x gravel chainrings to fit their own cranksets. Pairing a new Easton 1x ring to their lightweight &amp; versatile EC90 SL carbon or EA90 alloy cranks is likely to be one of the lightest, as well as best-looking cranksets to pair with a new custom GRX 12sp bike build…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Easton DM 1x chainrings for Shimano 12-speed HyperGlide+</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/2019-Shimano-XTR-12-speed-chain02-closeup.jpg\"><img width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/2019-Shimano-XTR-12-speed-chain02-closeup.jpg\" alt=\"Shimano XTR M9000 chain with dynamic chain engagement\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/2019-Shimano-XTR-12-speed-chain02-closeup.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/2019-Shimano-XTR-12-speed-chain02-closeup-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/2019-Shimano-XTR-12-speed-chain02-closeup-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/2019-Shimano-XTR-12-speed-chain02-closeup-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/2019-Shimano-XTR-12-speed-chain02-closeup-600x400.jpg 600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/2019-Shimano-XTR-12-speed-chain02-closeup-696x464.jpg 696w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/2019-Shimano-XTR-12-speed-chain02-closeup-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/2019-Shimano-XTR-12-speed-chain02-closeup-630x420.jpg 630w\" /></a><figcaption>Arrows point to the extended inner plate chamfers. Click to enlarge, we also shaded the two on the left in blue to better highlight the new shaping.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A peculiarity of Shimano’s 12-speed road, gravel &amp; mountain bike drivetrains is the HyperGlide+ chain. These are not compatible with previously universal narrow-wide chainring tooth profiles. The reason is the extension of the chamfer on the end of inner chain plates beyond the rollers. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_12sp-chain.jpg\"><img width=\"1000\" height=\"650\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_12sp-chain.jpg\" alt=\"Easton Direct Mount 1x GRX gravel chainrings for Shimano 12-speed 12sp HyperGlide+ chain\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_12sp-chain.jpg 1000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_12sp-chain-297x193.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_12sp-chain-800x520.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_12sp-chain-120x78.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_12sp-chain-768x499.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption><em>c. Easton</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve seen Shimano-specific 1x rings for MTB in the years since <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019-shimano-xtr-m9100-unveiled-this-changes-everything/\">XTR M9100’s debut</a>. But since the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-grx-12-speed-mechanical/\" target=\"_blank\">new GRX</a> is the first 12-speed Shimano road/gravel group specifically designed for 1x drivetrains, there hasn’t yet been a glut of narrow-wide chainring options for dropbar Shimano 12-speed bikes.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tech details</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_tooth-profiles.jpg\"><img width=\"1000\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_tooth-profiles.jpg\" alt=\"Easton Direct Mount 1x GRX gravel chainrings for Shimano 12-speed HyperGlide+ tooth profile\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_tooth-profiles.jpg 1000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_tooth-profiles-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_tooth-profiles-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_tooth-profiles-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_tooth-profiles-768x461.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Easton CNC-machines these new Direct Mount Shimano 12-speed chainrings from EA90 aluminum. And they get a 47mm chainline on Easton Cinch cranks. They are lightweight and available from 36-44T optimized for gravel riding, e.g. with a claimed weight of 90g for a 40T ring. Combine them with some $445 EC90 SL carbon cranks for a total crankset weight claim of just 442g (<em>172.5mm arms plus a 40T ring, without a BB</em>). Or pair to $125 aluminum EA90 arms for a more affordable setup that still weighs just 622g (<em>claimed 172.5mm, 40T, no BB</em>).</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Easton DM 12 chainrings – Pricing, Options &amp; Compatibility</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_36T.jpg\"><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_36T.jpg\" alt=\"Easton Direct Mount 1x GRX gravel chainrings for Shimano 12-speed HyperGlide+ 36T\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_36T.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_36T-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_36T-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_36T-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_36T-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_36T-1536x1536.jpg 1536w\" /></a><figcaption>36T</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_44T.jpg\"><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_44T.jpg\" alt=\"Easton Direct Mount 1x GRX gravel chainrings for Shimano 12-speed HyperGlide+ 44T\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_44T.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_44T-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_44T-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_44T-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_44T-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus_44T-1536x1536.jpg 1536w\" /></a><figcaption>44T</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Easton Direct Mount SHI 12 SPD chainrings retail for $85. The 12-speed Shimano rings come in 36, 38, 40, 42 &amp; 44-tooth variants, with claimed weight of 90g (40T).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus-with-EC90-SL-crankset.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus-with-EC90-SL-crankset.jpg\" alt=\"Easton Direct Mount 1x GRX gravel chainrings for Shimano 12-speed HyperGlide+ on EC90 SL cabron cranks\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus-with-EC90-SL-crankset.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus-with-EC90-SL-crankset-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus-with-EC90-SL-crankset-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus-with-EC90-SL-crankset-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus-with-EC90-SL-crankset-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Easton-DM-1x-GRX-gravel-chainrings-for-Shimano-12-speed-HyperGlidePlus-with-EC90-SL-crankset-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Easton DM rings are compatible with Cinch System cranks. That then explicitly includes Easton’s own EC90 SL &amp; EA90 cranks, but also RaceFace cranks with their resulting MTB chainlines. The new rings are also compatible with all Shimano 12-speed groupsets for road, gravel, and mountain bike drivetrains.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Easton machines new direct mount 1x gravel chainrings for Shimano 12-speed road &amp; gravel groups – i.e. from GRX &amp; 105 to Dura-Ace…</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://eastoncycling.com/\" target=\"_blank\">EastonCycling.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/easton-direct-mount-shimano-12-speed-1x-chainrings/\">Easton 1x Direct Mount 12sp Chainrings Mate Cinch Cranks to GRX, 105, Ultegra &amp; Dura-Ace</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"68908a36a2ef89677f2591bfa263f9871e4351f639de424eb3323055dd158e8d","category":"Cycling"}